      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:5:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) شِرَارُ نِسَائِكُمُ الْمُعْقَرَةُ الدَّنِسَةُ اللَّجُوجَةُ الْعَاصِيَةُ الذَّلِيلَةُ فِي قَوْمِهَا الْعَزِيزَةُ فِي نَفْسِهَا الْحَصَانُ عَلَى زَوْجِهَا الْهَلُوكُ عَلَى غَيْرِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from one of his companions, from Milhan, from Abdullah Bin Sinan who said, ",
          "‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The most evil of your women is the barren, the profane, the insistent, the disobedient, the disgraceful among her people, the dear regarding herself, the preserved upon her husband, the craver upon others’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn Khalid from certain persons of his people from Milhan from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sinan who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, has said, ‘The wicked ones of your women is one who is barren, filthy, quarrelsome, disobedient, undignified among her people and honored to herself, reserved in the presence of her husband but shows others to be of great carnal appetite.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
